"{\"value\":{\"mdx\":\"# ZK Proof Details\\n\\nThe SP1 program proves the following:\\n1. The photo bytes matches the expected bytes in the C2PA manifest\\n2. The Apple Attest attestation is valid\\n3. The assertion (i.e. signature of the photo hash using the attested key) is valid\\n\\nThe photo bytes are provided as input to the proof.\\n\\n## Proof Logic\\n\\n| Step | Operation | Guarantees |\\n|------|-----------|------------|\\n| 1 | Extract manifest from photo bytes | — |\\n| 2 | Extract bindings and data hash from manifest | — |\\n| 3 | Compute photo hash | — |\\n| 4 | Check data hash == photo hash | Manifest corresponds to this photo |\\n| 5 | Validate attestation | The attestation is valid and from Apple |\\n| 6 | Validate assertion | Photo hash was signed by the attested key |\\n\\n## Attestation Validation\\n\\nGuarantees:\\n- The device key was generated in a genuine Apple Secure Enclave\\n- The key is bound to a specific app (via `app_id` / RP ID)\\n- The device is running a legitimate app (AAGUID = `appattest` or `appattestdevelop`)\\n\\nValidates:\\n- Certificate chain verifies up to Apple Root CA\\n- Nonce matches the challenge\\n- Public key hash matches the key ID\\n- RP ID == SHA256(app_id)\\n- AAGUID is a valid Apple attestation identifier\\n\\n## Assertion Validation\\n\\nGuarantees:\\n- The photo corresponding to this hash was signed using the ZCAM SDK\\n\\nValidates:\\n- ECDSA signature over the photo hash using the public key from attestation\\n\\n## Public Outputs\\n- Photo hash (SHA-256)\\n- Apple Root CA certificate\\n\\nThese committed values allow verifiers to confirm the proof corresponds to a specific photo and chains to Apple's actual root certificate.\\n\",\"document\":[{\"href\":\"/technical-docs/zkproof-details#zk-proof-details\",\"html\":\"</header>\\n<p>The SP1 program proves the following:</p>\\n<ol>\\n<li>The photo bytes matches the expected bytes in the C2PA manifest</li>\\n<li>The Apple Attest attestation is valid</li>\\n<li>The assertion (i.e. signature of the photo hash using the attested key) is valid</li>\\n</ol>\\n<p>The photo bytes are provided as input to the proof.</p>\\n\",\"id\":\"docs/pages/technical-docs/zkproof-details.mdx#zk-proof-details\",\"isPage\":true,\"text\":\"\\nThe SP1 program proves the following:\\n\\nThe photo bytes matches the expected bytes in the C2PA manifest\\nThe Apple Attest attestation is valid\\nThe assertion (i.e. signature of the photo hash using the attested key) is valid\\n\\nThe photo bytes are provided as input to the proof.\\n\",\"title\":\"ZK Proof Details\",\"titles\":[]},{\"href\":\"/technical-docs/zkproof-details#proof-logic\",\"html\":\"\\n<table><thead><tr><th>Step</th><th>Operation</th><th>Guarantees</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>1</td><td>Extract manifest from photo bytes</td><td>—</td></tr><tr><td>2</td><td>Extract bindings and data hash from manifest</td><td>—</td></tr><tr><td>3</td><td>Compute photo hash</td><td>—</td></tr><tr><td>4</td><td>Check data hash == photo hash</td><td>Manifest corresponds to this photo</td></tr><tr><td>5</td><td>Validate attestation</td><td>The attestation is valid and from Apple</td></tr><tr><td>6</td><td>Validate assertion</td><td>Photo hash was signed by the attested key</td></tr></tbody></table>\\n\",\"id\":\"docs/pages/technical-docs/zkproof-details.mdx#proof-logic\",\"isPage\":false,\"text\":\"\\nStepOperationGuarantees1Extract manifest from photo bytes—2Extract bindings and data hash from manifest—3Compute photo hash—4Check data hash == photo hashManifest corresponds to this photo5Validate attestationThe attestation is valid and from Apple6Validate assertionPhoto hash was signed by the attested key\\n\",\"title\":\"Proof Logic\",\"titles\":[\"ZK Proof Details\"]},{\"href\":\"/technical-docs/zkproof-details#attestation-validation\",\"html\":\"\\n<p>Guarantees:</p>\\n<ul>\\n<li>The device key was generated in a genuine Apple Secure Enclave</li>\\n<li>The key is bound to a specific app (via <code>app_id</code> / RP ID)</li>\\n<li>The device is running a legitimate app (AAGUID = <code>appattest</code> or <code>appattestdevelop</code>)</li>\\n</ul>\\n<p>Validates:</p>\\n<ul>\\n<li>Certificate chain verifies up to Apple Root CA</li>\\n<li>Nonce matches the challenge</li>\\n<li>Public key hash matches the key ID</li>\\n<li>RP ID == SHA256(app_id)</li>\\n<li>AAGUID is a valid Apple attestation identifier</li>\\n</ul>\\n\",\"id\":\"docs/pages/technical-docs/zkproof-details.mdx#attestation-validation\",\"isPage\":false,\"text\":\"\\nGuarantees:\\n\\nThe device key was generated in a genuine Apple Secure Enclave\\nThe key is bound to a specific app (via app_id / RP ID)\\nThe device is running a legitimate app (AAGUID = appattest or appattestdevelop)\\n\\nValidates:\\n\\nCertificate chain verifies up to Apple Root CA\\nNonce matches the challenge\\nPublic key hash matches the key ID\\nRP ID == SHA256(app_id)\\nAAGUID is a valid Apple attestation identifier\\n\\n\",\"title\":\"Attestation Validation\",\"titles\":[\"ZK Proof Details\"]},{\"href\":\"/technical-docs/zkproof-details#assertion-validation\",\"html\":\"\\n<p>Guarantees:</p>\\n<ul>\\n<li>The photo corresponding to this hash was signed using the ZCAM SDK</li>\\n</ul>\\n<p>Validates:</p>\\n<ul>\\n<li>ECDSA signature over the photo hash using the public key from attestation</li>\\n</ul>\\n\",\"id\":\"docs/pages/technical-docs/zkproof-details.mdx#assertion-validation\",\"isPage\":false,\"text\":\"\\nGuarantees:\\n\\nThe photo corresponding to this hash was signed using the ZCAM SDK\\n\\nValidates:\\n\\nECDSA signature over the photo hash using the public key from attestation\\n\\n\",\"title\":\"Assertion Validation\",\"titles\":[\"ZK Proof Details\"]},{\"href\":\"/technical-docs/zkproof-details#public-outputs\",\"html\":\"\\n<ul>\\n<li>Photo hash (SHA-256)</li>\\n<li>Apple Root CA certificate</li>\\n</ul>\\n<p>These committed values allow verifiers to confirm the proof corresponds to a specific photo and chains to Apple&#x27;s actual root certificate.</p>\",\"id\":\"docs/pages/technical-docs/zkproof-details.mdx#public-outputs\",\"isPage\":false,\"text\":\"\\n\\nPhoto hash (SHA-256)\\nApple Root CA certificate\\n\\nThese committed values allow verifiers to confirm the proof corresponds to a specific photo and chains to Apple&#x27;s actual root certificate.\",\"title\":\"Public Outputs\",\"titles\":[\"ZK Proof Details\"]}]}}"
